# Normalize all text to LF in every working tree, on every platform.
# Several tests compare a committed file byte-for-byte against generated output
# that uses `\n` only (the descriptor golden snapshot and the committed JSON
# schema, embedded via include_str!). Windows CI runners default
# core.autocrlf=true, which would otherwise check those out as CRLF and break the
# compare. Pinning eol=lf makes the build platform-independent.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never touch their bytes.
*.tosc binary
*.wav binary
